      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780261102149" href="/book/show/28854.The_Book_of_Lost_Tales_Part_Two">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3799340702" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11346159516961881403">A nice introduction to all three great tales for those not familiar with them. But the highlight is certainly “The History of Eriol or Ælfwine and the End of the Tales.” This is arguably where the early conceptions most drastically differed from the later ones, making this a particularly interesting stage of the mythology’s evolution.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


