    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_20397326" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/20397326" />
    <a title="Othy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/868069-othy"><img alt="Othy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1435444371p2/868069.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/20397326?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Othy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Othy" href="/user/show/868069-othy">Othy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780395426401" href="/book/show/77677.The_Book_of_Lost_Tales_Part_Two_The_History_of_Middle_Earth_2_">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/868069-othy?shelf=fantasy-literature">fantasy-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/868069-othy?shelf=tolkien">tolkien</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer20397326" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7948730808362549703">Though I liked the first Book of Lost Tales better, this one was still amazing. The stories in it not only give depth to the Silmarillion and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34.The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring__The_Lord_of_the_Rings__Part_1_' title='The Fellowship of the Ring (The Lord of the Rings, Part 1) by J.R.R. Tolkien' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Lord of the Rings</a>, but also as JRR Tolkien himself AND what being a human and an artist really means. Some of the work of both prose and poetry in this volume is equal in beauty to the most wonderfully beautiful pieces Tolkien himself published. Anyone who enjoys writing in any form should read these tales.</span>
  <span id="freeText7948730808362549703" style="display:none">Though I liked the first Book of Lost Tales better, this one was still amazing. The stories in it not only give depth to the Silmarillion and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34.The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring__The_Lord_of_the_Rings__Part_1_" title="The Fellowship of the Ring (The Lord of the Rings, Part 1) by J.R.R. Tolkien" rel="nofollow noopener">The Lord of the Rings</a>, but also as JRR Tolkien himself AND what being a human and an artist really means. Some of the work of both prose and poetry in this volume is equal in beauty to the most wonderfully beautiful pieces Tolkien himself published. Anyone who enjoys writing in any form should read these tales.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7948730808362549703" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


